  "prompt": "What is the best all round fighter jet as of 2015?",
  "response": "As of 2015, the F-22 Raptor is often considered one of the best all-around fighter jets. Developed by Lockheed Martin for the United States Air Force, the F-22 features advanced stealth capabilities, supercruise (the ability to fly at supersonic speeds without afterburners), and cutting-edge avionics. Its combination of speed, maneuverability, and electronic warfare capabilities makes it highly effective in various combat scenarios.\n\nAnother notable contender at that time was the F-35 Lightning II, which is designed to be a multirole stealth fighter and is intended to serve various branches of the U.S. military and allied nations. The F-35 has advanced technologies, including sensors and networking capabilities, allowing it to operate effectively in joint operations.\n\nUltimately, the \u201cbest\u201d fighter jet can depend on specific mission requirements, operational capabilities, and the context in which it is employed.",
